    Key insights (per the agent prompt):
      1. THIS IS THE ONLY DEMO TASK WITH status=In Progress. All other
         seven tasks are either Open or Closed. This task is the
         canonical demonstrator for the middle status state and proves
         that the case_task status Choice list correctly accepts the
         In Progress value as a registered third option. Without this
         task, the dataset would lack any In Progress demonstration,
         leaving the choice list's middle value untested.
      2. THE STATUS In Progress HAS A SPACE. Most common error point.
         The choice list defines it as "In Progress" (Title Case,
         single space). The resolve gate's GlideRecord query compares
         status != 'Closed' (case-sensitive negated equality), so
         In Progress is correctly counted as non-Closed. Any of the
         common typo variants (InProgress, In_Progress, in progress,
         IN PROGRESS, In  Progress with double space) would either
         cause an insert-time choice-list rejection or break the
         resolve-blocker logic; the verbatim "In Progress" value is
         load-bearing.
      3. THIS TASK + TASK 07 BLOCK CASE 08 RESOLUTION. Together they
         exercise the complaint flow's resolve-blocker. The verbatim
         error "All tasks must be closed before resolving this case."
         must fire when the operator attempts case 08 -> Resolved.
         Where tasks 01 + 02 perform this role for case 03 on the
         General Inquiry flow, tasks 06 + 07 perform it for case 08
         on the Complaint flow.
      4. THE +7 DAYS DUE_DATE reflects the longer time-horizon of
         investigation work on a Complaint case. Case 08 is Critical
         priority but the investigation timeframe is realistic - an
         agent expects roughly a week of active work on the broader
         investigation. This contrasts with task 07's +3 days (a
         specific upcoming witness-interview prep step), reinforcing
         that broader investigations span longer than their constituent
         steps.
      5. THE Investigation TYPE matches the "Complaint investigation"
         semantics in the subject. Tasks 01 and 06 both use the
         Investigation type (one on a General Inquiry case, one on a
         Complaint case), demonstrating consistency of the Investigation
         type across both flow paths. Task 04 also uses Investigation
         (on a Resolved General Inquiry case) and task 07 uses
         Investigation (on case 08 alongside this task), so the
         Investigation type appears 4 times total across the 8 tasks
         - the most common task type.
      6. NO PII. The "Complaint investigation" subject is generic.
         "Complaint" is a case-type Choice label per AAP Section 0.5.7,
         not a person's name or specific incident description.
         "Investigation" is a generic agent-action noun. No real
         names, real email addresses, real phone numbers, or real
         organization names appear anywhere in this file.
      7. BUILD AGENT COMPUTES due_date DYNAMICALLY at file-generation
         time so that the relative offset (+7 days) is preserved
         across importation timeframes. The actual stored value
         (2026-05-08) is the static result of today + 7 days
         evaluated at this file's generation time (today =
         2026-05-01 per the build environment date).
